<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Female</emphasis>
(Paratype). General features and coloration similar to those of male (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Psiloderces pingguo sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, lateral view D male habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, dorsal view F female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviations: PR = clypeal protrusion, SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370856" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">12E, F</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 1.56; carapace 0.47 long, 0.55 wide; abdomen 1.09 long, 0.86 wide. Leg measurements: I-IV missing. Endogyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Psiloderces pingguo sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, lateral view D male habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, dorsal view F female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviations: PR = clypeal protrusion, SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370856" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">12A</figureCitation>
): spermathecae stalked, with globose distal part, globose part almost as wide as stalk, stalks 4 times longer than globose part, spermathecae anteriorly elliptical with a pair of tubular ducts (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Psiloderces pingguo sp. nov., male holotype and female paratype. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, lateral view D male habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, dorsal view F female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviations: PR = clypeal protrusion, SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.902.38967.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/370856" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
